         <OBJECT_CONTRACT>
            <TITLE>
               <P>TfL 93585 Apprentice Training – Engineering Framework</P>
            </TITLE>
            <REFERENCE_NUMBER>DN324843</REFERENCE_NUMBER>
            <CPV_MAIN>
               <CPV_CODE CODE="80000000"/>
            </CPV_MAIN>
            <TYPE_CONTRACT CTYPE="SERVICES"/>
            <SHORT_DESCR>
               <P>TfL require an Engineering apprenticeship framework, this will be an initial 2 year agreement with an option to extend for a further 2 years (1+1) and will be divided into 2 Lots.</P>
            </SHORT_DESCR>
            <VAL_ESTIMATED_TOTAL CURRENCY="GBP">2650000</VAL_ESTIMATED_TOTAL>
            <LOT_DIVISION>
               <LOT_ALL/>
            </LOT_DIVISION>
            <OBJECT_DESCR ITEM="1">
               <TITLE>
                  <P>Lot 1: Engineering (Level 2-5)</P>
               </TITLE>
               <LOT_NO>1</LOT_NO>
               <CPV_ADDITIONAL>
                  <CPV_CODE CODE="80300000"/>
               </CPV_ADDITIONAL>
               <CPV_ADDITIONAL>
                  <CPV_CODE CODE="80400000"/>
               </CPV_ADDITIONAL>
               <CPV_ADDITIONAL>
                  <CPV_CODE CODE="80500000"/>
               </CPV_ADDITIONAL>
               <n2016:NUTS CODE="UKI"/>
               <SHORT_DESCR>
                  <P>TfL require an Engineering apprenticeship framework, this will be an initial 2 year contract with an option to extended for a further 2 years (1+1). Lot 1 will include, but not limited to the apprenticeship standards listed below:</P>
                  <P>Lot 1: Engineering (Level 2-5).</P>
                  <P>— Civil engineering technician (estimated intake of 4 per annum).</P>
                  <P>— Rail engineering technician (estimated intake of 5 per annum).</P>
                  <P>— Rail infrastructure operator (estimated intake of 2 per annum).</P>
                  <P>— Engineering design and draughtsperson (estimated intake of 4 per annum).</P>
                  <P>— Railway engineering design technician (estimated intake of 4 per annum).</P>
                  <P>— Rail engineering advanced technician (estimated intake of 2 per annum).</P>
               </SHORT_DESCR>
               <AC_PROCUREMENT_DOC/>
               <DURATION TYPE="MONTH">48</DURATION>
               <RENEWAL/>
               <RENEWAL_DESCR>
                  <P>It is likely that the arrangement will be renewed, retendered near the end of its term.</P>
               </RENEWAL_DESCR>
               <NO_ACCEPTED_VARIANTS/>
               <OPTIONS/>
               <OPTIONS_DESCR>
                  <P>Following the initial 2 year contract period, the contract may be renewed for a further 2 years (1+1) at the sole discretion of the Contracting Authority.</P>
               </OPTIONS_DESCR>
               <NO_EU_PROGR_RELATED/>
            </OBJECT_DESCR>
            <OBJECT_DESCR ITEM="2">
               <TITLE>
                  <P>Lot 2: Engineering (Level 6+)</P>
               </TITLE>
               <LOT_NO>2</LOT_NO>
               <CPV_ADDITIONAL>
                  <CPV_CODE CODE="80300000"/>
               </CPV_ADDITIONAL>
               <CPV_ADDITIONAL>
                  <CPV_CODE CODE="80400000"/>
               </CPV_ADDITIONAL>
               <CPV_ADDITIONAL>
                  <CPV_CODE CODE="80500000"/>
               </CPV_ADDITIONAL>
               <n2016:NUTS CODE="UKI"/>
               <SHORT_DESCR>
                  <P>TfL require an Engineering apprenticeship framework, this will be an initial 2 year contract with an option to extended for a further 2 years (1+1). Lot 2 will include, but not limited to the apprenticeship standards listed below:</P>
                  <P>Lot 2 Engineering (Level 6+).</P>
                  <P>— Civil engineer degree (estimated intake of 4 per annum).</P>
                  <P>— Embedded electronic systems design and development engineer (estimated intake of 2 per annum).</P>
               </SHORT_DESCR>
               <AC_PROCUREMENT_DOC/>
